I used to live and work in that area in the late 90s It was called Famous Pita then After I moved away in 1999 I have traveled in and out of USA. When I moved to Texas every shawarma I tested just does not taste like the real one Famous Pita. Then in 2006 when I was pregnant I was craving real shawarma and I called my friend who lives in Brooklyn to buy $100 worth for and ship it to me next day delivery. I spent over $100 but it was worth it I have traveled to many place in the USA and even in the Middle East no shawarma has ever tasted so good as this shawarma I Am currently visiting Los Angeles and I still cannot find any shawarma like this. Perhaps before I go back to west Africa I will find a way to get the best Sharwama in the entire world If not may God spare my life to next year and beyond I would find a way go come to the Big Apple

They also can apply to the Guinness book of records for minute size of their portions. And, when ordering from a restaurant, should you receive a complete order? Well, it depends... My order from Olympia Pita was missing a main entry. Finally, for those folks who remember that falafel normally looks and tastes like...falafel, please don't be shocked when you instead find small dry burned pieces of chickpeas in your Olympia Pita order. When called asking about my missing entry, I was assured I would get a equivalent discount in price for it in my next order from the restaurant.  Thanks but no thanks Olympia Pita.
